    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond</placeName> <date>January 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">Doubtlessly long since<lb/> you have given up all idea of receiving a reply to yours&#44; when<lb/> I received in due time&#44; &#38; would apologize to you&#44; if I knew<lb/> what excuse to make&#44; but to you I need but <sic>acknoledge</sic> my<lb/> remissness &#38; I know you will excuse me&#44; although I have in<lb/> part some slight excuse to offer&#44; that is my business anxieties<lb/> have engrossed the whole of my attention&#44; so that neither <persName>Mr.<lb/> S. Heyman</persName> or myself have had sufficient unoccupied time<lb/> to attend to your matters here. Our congregation matters are<lb/> at a very low ebb&#44; in consequence of not sufficient energy<lb/> in all of its members. I almost feel that we can never thrive<lb/> again&#44; many of our members are going over to the other Congre&#45;<lb/>&#45;gation &#38; for the two last Sabbaths&#44; we have not had<lb/> Minyan in Shool Until we get a good Hazan&#44; one who<lb/> is in every way competent to inspire us with religious feeling<lb/> &#38; one whom we can respect &#38; look up to for instruction&#44; we<lb/> must continue to decrease.</p>
			<p>I must again say that if you had an enterprising agent<lb/> here&#44; that a good deal could be done with your various works<lb/> &#38; really I do not know whom to advise you to appoint&#44; as<lb/> <persName>Mr. S. Hyman</persName> will leave <placeName>Richmond</placeName> in a few weeks to<lb/> enter business in <placeName>Petersburg</placeName> with <persName>Michael Davis</persName>&#44; son of<lb/> <persName>Goodman Davis</persName>&#44; consequently you cannot obtain his<lb/> services. As regards the Jewish Publication Society&#44; that</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>with all other religious matters as I before remarked&#44; are&#44; at<lb/> a very low Ebb&#44; there has not been a meeting of that Society<lb/> for more than a year and half&#59; all &#38; every thing is in a very<lb/> deplorable state In looking over list of your Delinquents I am<lb/> sorry to inform you that many of your Claims you will<lb/> not realize one Cent from&#44; as regards the among against<lb/> me&#44; I have always understood that <persName>Jacob Ezekiel</persName> gave me<lb/> credit for the amount&#44; this is the case with many others to<lb/> whom <persName>Ezekiel&#39;s</persName> hands until you can get an agent&#44; for as<lb/> long as they remain in his possession&#44; you must necessarily<lb/> loose. We are all Thank God in usual Health&#44; excepting<lb/> Father&#44; who is suffering from scalded feet</p>
			<p>Wishing you Health Prosperity</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">I remain</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">your Friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Isaac A Levy</persName></p>
			<p><persName>Mrs. Levy</persName> desires her regards.</p>
			<p>P.S. Since writing the above&#44; I have conversed with <persName>Mr.<lb/> N. Ezekiel</persName>&#44; who is willing to undertake the agency.</p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p><placeName>371 Walnut Street</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          
        </body>
